  "texts": [
    "While effective in controlled settings, these methods often required manual feature selection and were limited in their ability to adapt across varying sample types and conditions.",
    "Early electronic nose systems, based on rule-based algorithms, also struggled with nonlinearity, sensor drift, and background noise, which hindered real-world performance.",
    "The adoption of AI has addressed many of these challenges by enabling data-driven modeling, improving generalizability, and revealing complex patterns within high-dimensional olfactory datasets.",
    "This shift from static rule-based systems to adaptive learning frameworks marks a major evolution in olfactory research, offering more robust, scalable, and context-aware analytical capabilities.",
    "The integration of AI into olfactory data analysis has emerged as a transformative trend, leveraging advanced computational techniques to decode the complexities of chemical signals."
